"/> I don't go to website links from newsgroups, you should have posted the
text here. However I don't make offers either. To me, when I ask
someone how much something is, and they say &quot;Make an offer&quot; it is an
insult, as he is hoping that I will say a price that is higher than he
might have asked, and get more money out of me. Anytime one DOES give
an offer, the seller just laughs at you anyway and tells you to keep
walking, or some other insult. I always get the last laugh when I see
the same seller a year later trying to sell the same item.

If I don't see a price ON the item being sold, I don't even bother to go
through the silly game of asking. I assume the item is not for sale and
move to the next table, as if it was for sale, it would have a price tag
on it. I am usually right, as the &quot;sellers&quot; always end up bringing the
items home with them and bring them back for &quot;show&quot; many times for
years.

