I'm going to share a secret with you folks that my dear departed grandmother (
who was also my boss &amp; mentor ) used to use in a standoff situation with people
who had merchandise for sale that they didn't know what to ask for it or even
if they really wanted to sell it. ( This is assuming it's something you really
want. ) Tell the seller we're going to play a little game, get 2 pieces of
paper &amp; give one to the seller &amp; you keep one. Now tell the seller to write a
price on the paper that would make them happy &amp; you write your price that your
willing to offer &amp; keep them hidden. Now tell the seller we'll both reveal our
prices &amp; if mine is higher than yours you will sell the piece to me at my price
if not than the deal is off &amp; you can say thank you &amp; leave. Then flip the
papers &amp; see what happens. Now even if your price is not higher than theirs at
least you have an idea of what price this person is thinking &amp; may lead to
further negotiations or you may run out of the house screaming ! At minimum
you have gotten the seller to commit to something &amp; started the negotiation
process. Besides people love games &amp; will usually play along. This is part of
the legacy I pass on from Carrie Ruggles may she RIP. David

