I never ask about unpriced items I see at shows. I guess I may have missed out
on a lot of great deals, but I always expect the dealers price to be on an
item. I feel at an unfair advantage somehow, revealing to the dealer that the
item interests me enough to ask its price. But at garage sales when I find an
unmarked item I like, I make an offer without even asking the price. In that
case, I figure the person either overlooked it or didn't know what to ask, so I
just make an offer.
In the case of online items where either no price is given or they state &quot;make
me an offer&quot;, in most cases I ignore such posts. I agree that lots of time the
person is looking for an appraisal and I have been in situations where I ended
up bidding on something against some unknown and possibly nonexistant person
and ended up feeling used. Since ebay came along there is no need to get
involved in such blind auctions.
