an item with NO sticker and asks &quot;how much?&quot; All of my
items are priced (I check while I'm setting up to make sure that
everything has a clean and proper price tag and I retag all
items that need one.) And....those &quot;missing&quot; price tags turn
up in the most curious places (stuck on another item, dropped
on the floor/ground, stuck on a tablecloth, etc.) Some of the
items brought to me have obviously had the sticker torn off
(there's residue of the paper) -- and it's obvious that the
sticker just didn't fall off.

Since I always have my notebook computer with me, all I have
to do is let them watch me check the sales price. And I let them
watch me put a new tag ON the item.

Do they ever buy the item? Nope.
Do they make a counter-offer? Nope.
They're hoping, obviously, for a &quot;guesstimate&quot; -- and since
the tag is immediately replaced, it's obvious that my selling
price IS my selling price (and my prices are quite reasonable.)

